            <h4 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">Your Benefits: Learn about the services &amp; benefits available to you from the Government of Canada â for Youth, Seniors Newcomers, and families With Craig Graham, Citizen Service Specialist â Service Canada </h4> <ul><li>Tuesday March 22, 3:00 - 4:00 &amp; 6:00 - 7:00pm at the Pictou Library</li><li> Tuesday March 29, 6:15 - 7:15pm at the River John Library</li>
            </ul>
                 </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
            <p>What is Service Canada?</p><p>Service Canada is an organisation that provides a âone stop shopâ for government programs and services for Citizens whether they are Seniors, Youth, Newcomers to Canada, or from the Aboriginal Community.<br>Service Canada is about serving you better by bringing together information on most Government of Canada programs and services under one umbrella. Service Canada gives you one website to visit, one main phone number to call and a network of Service Canada Offices and Outreach sites where employees are trained to help you find the information you need.<br>This presentation will highlight the many service offerings Service Canada has for you including how to navigate the website â<a href="http://www.canadabenefits.gc.ca/" target="_blank">canadabenefits.gc.ca</a>â.</p><p>All are welcome!</p><p>Please call 902 485-5021 (Pictou Library) or 902 351-2599 (River John Library) for more information or to pre-register.</p>
