            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">            
<p><strong>Seniors Cafe</strong> at the <strong>Antigonish Library Wednesday, March 2, 2:00pm - 3:00pm presents 'Highland Storytellers - A reading and commentary' with author Teresa MacIsaac</strong> This month, Teresa MacIssac will be introducing her new book 'Highland Storytellers.' The book follows a family who have immigrated to Nova Scotia from the Highlands of Scotland through four generations. Described as 'creative non-fiction' this book is a highly researched saga of the Highland immigrants of the early 1800s.  Fun, informal sessions. Full access to library services. All are welcome, and light refreshments will be served. For more information or for program suggestions, call (902) 863-4276.</p>
<p><strong>Seniors Cafe</strong> at the <strong>Westville Library Wednesday, March 2nd, 2:30pm presents âBiopulsar Technologyâ: a marriage of the mind, body and spirit, </strong>with speaker  Cindy Rolston Hemphill, from the White Lotus. This month, Cindy will talk about (and demonstrate) Biopulsar technology with a machine that gives an empirical measurement of the health of peopleâs organs, and shows how peopleâs thoughts and emotions have an impact on their physical health. About the speaker: Cindy Rorison Hemphill is owner of The White Lotus, a local business in downtown New Glasgow. She started the business to share her interest in the magic of whatâs seen and the mysteries of whatâs unseen. All are welcome! Fun, informal sessions. Full access to library services &amp; light refreshments served! For more information please call 902 396-5022.</p>
<p><strong>Seniors Now</strong> at the <strong>New Glasgow Library Thursday, March 10 at 1:30pm presents âEye to Eyeâ â Things to keep in mind as your eyesight ages,</strong> with Dr. Melanie Reid, Optometrist<br>Join us during World Glaucoma Week as local optometrist Dr. Melanie Reid talks about eyesight, and reasons for vision loss related to aging. She will also chat about things we can do to keep our vision working to the best of itâs capability.<br>About the speaker: Melanie earned her Bachelor of Science with honours and Doctor of
Optometry degrees from the University of Waterloo in Ontario. During the four-year optometry program, she conducted an external study placement in St. Petersburg, Florida and another in Houston, Texas to study ocular disease. She is a certified therapeutic optometrist and is licensed to treat ocular disease. While she, her husband Nathan and their family reside in New Glasgow, Reid Optometry has locations in Antigonish, New Glasgow and Truro. All are welcome! For more information please call 902 752-8233.</p>
<p><strong>Seniors Cafe</strong> at the <strong>Pictou Library Monday, March 21st 10:00 - 11:30am presents Easter Decorating</strong>. This month, the morning will be filled with lots of Easter celebrations, including egg decorating and more! Light refreshments are provided. All are welcome! For more information please call 902 485-5021.</p>
