<!--Sixth modal-->
<div class="modal fade" id="sixthModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="basicModal" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
            <h4 class="modal-title" id="sixthModal">
       Lead poisoning in Wildlife &amp; Non-Lead Angling &amp; Hunting with speaker Helene Van Doninck, DVM<p><ul><li>Tuesday March 29 (6:30pm) â Westville Library</li><li>Thursday March 31 (7:00pm) â Antigonish Library</li><li>Thursday April 7 (7:00pm) â Pictou Library</li><li>Thursday April 14 (6:30pm) â River John Library</li></ul></h4>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
               <p>Lead poisoning in wildlife happens where lead based ammunition and fishing tackle are used. People can also unintentionally ingest lead by eating lead harvested game. Come and learn about this issue and ways to solve this easily preventable problem, by voluntarily switching to non-lead ammo and tackle. We'll also talk about the non-lead ammo and tackle exchange program in Nova Scotia.</p><p><strong>About the speaker:</strong> Helene Van Doninck is the volunteer veterinarian and co-founder of the Cobequid Wildlife Rehabilitation Centre in Hilden, NS. She has been providing lead poisoning outreach to hunters, anglers, and the general public since 2011. She has lectured on this topic in Atlantic Canada and the United States and is thrilled that Nova Scotia is a North American leader in this initiative.</p><p>All are welcome!</p> 
</div>
